<p>Apache::ASP has been in development since 1998, and was production ready since its .02 release. Releases are always used in a production setting before being made publically available.</p>

<p>In July 2000, the version numbers of releases went from .19 to 1.9 which is more relevant to software development outside the perl community. Where a .10 perl module usually means first production ready release, this would be the equivalent of a 1.0 release for other kinds of software.</p>

<pre class="sh_perl"> + = improvement   - = bug fix    (d) = documentations</pre>

